place.name: SWANTON NOVERS
place.gazetteerText: SWANTON-NOVERS, a parish in Walsingham district, Norfolk; 5 miles N E by E of Ryburgh r. station. Post town, Briningham, under Thetford. Acres, 1,315. Real property, £2,105. Pop., 315. houses, 68. S. house is the seat ofAtkinson, Esq. The living is a rectory, annexed to Wood-Norton. The church's chancel was rebuilt in 1821. There is a Wesleyan chapel. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
